ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class is not a fun one to take, though if you're a graduate student in physics, you'll have to take it! I wouldn't recommend this professor to another person.
I would recommend taking this class.
Gotta take it, hopefully with someone else teaching.
The first half of the course was useful, the second half not so much.
It was a course where you needed to learn the material by yourself first and then you might appreciate what the instructor says, otherwise it's a bit difficult to get a lot out of the course
I wouldn't recommend physics 512. In the end I don't think I learned that much from it and it overall wasn't a very pleasant experience.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I managed to learn something by studying on my own, but I don't feel like I gained an awful lot from this course.
The material for this class is very relevant towards my future research and this class met my expectations of what I wanted to learn.
Not particularly. I think I would have done just as well on the final at the beginning of the course.

This class have made me gain a lot of insight about Statistical Physics. Before the class I knew how to approach a given HMK problem, but the class has helped me understand the underlying physics that it is trying to explain.
i learned some basic stat mech, though some of the more advanced stuff escaped me.
Now, I have more deep understanding for classical statistical mechanics and comfortable about relationship between each ensemble, and I would like to know more about this subject in future.
I learned something in this course, but I expected more. Thanks anyway
I think it will be helpful, but again more problems would have been helpful.
